v8
V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

61// Provides JavaScript-specific "macro-assembler" functionality on top of the
62// CodeAssembler. By factoring the JavaScript-isms out of the CodeAssembler,
63// it's possible to add JavaScript-specific useful CodeAssembler "macros"
64// without modifying files in the compiler directory (and requiring a review
65// from a compiler directory OWNER).
66class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE CodeStubAssembler
67 : public compiler::CodeAssembler,
68 public TorqueGeneratedExportedMacrosAssembler {
69 public:
70 using ScopedExceptionHandler = compiler::ScopedExceptionHandler;
71
72 template <typename T>
73 using LazyNode = std::function<TNode<T>()>;
74
75 explicit CodeStubAssembler(compiler::CodeAssemblerState* state);

219#define PARAMETER_BINOP(OpName, IntPtrOpName, SmiOpName) \
220 TNode<Smi> OpName(TNode<Smi> a, TNode<Smi> b) { return SmiOpName(a, b); } \
221 TNode<IntPtrT> OpName(TNode<IntPtrT> a, TNode<IntPtrT> b) { \
222 return IntPtrOpName(a, b); \
223 } \
224 TNode<UintPtrT> OpName(TNode<UintPtrT> a, TNode<UintPtrT> b) { \
225 return Unsigned(IntPtrOpName(Signed(a), Signed(b))); \
226 } \
227 TNode<RawPtrT> OpName(TNode<RawPtrT> a, TNode<RawPtrT> b) { \
228 return ReinterpretCast<RawPtrT>(IntPtrOpName( \
229 ReinterpretCast<IntPtrT>(a), ReinterpretCast<IntPtrT>(b))); \
230 }
231 // TODO(v8:9708): Define BInt operations once all uses are ported.
232 PARAMETER_BINOP(IntPtrOrSmiAdd, IntPtrAdd, SmiAdd)
233 PARAMETER_BINOP(IntPtrOrSmiSub, IntPtrSub, SmiSub)
234#undef PARAMETER_BINOP
235
236#define PARAMETER_BINOP(OpName, IntPtrOpName, SmiOpName) \
237 TNode<BoolT> OpName(TNode<Smi> a, TNode<Smi> b) { return SmiOpName(a, b); } \
238 TNode<BoolT> OpName(TNode<IntPtrT> a, TNode<IntPtrT> b) { \
239 return IntPtrOpName(a, b); \
240 } \
241 /* IntPtrXXX comparisons shouldn't be used with unsigned types, use */ \
242 /* UintPtrXXX operations explicitly instead. */ \
243 TNode<BoolT> OpName(TNode<UintPtrT> a, TNode<UintPtrT> b) { UNREACHABLE(); } \
244 TNode<BoolT> OpName(TNode<RawPtrT> a, TNode<RawPtrT> b) { UNREACHABLE(); }
245 // TODO(v8:9708): Define BInt operations once all uses are ported.
246 PARAMETER_BINOP(IntPtrOrSmiEqual, WordEqual, SmiEqual)
247 PARAMETER_BINOP(IntPtrOrSmiNotEqual, WordNotEqual, SmiNotEqual)
248 PARAMETER_BINOP(IntPtrOrSmiLessThan, IntPtrLessThan, SmiLessThan)
249 PARAMETER_BINOP(IntPtrOrSmiLessThanOrEqual, IntPtrLessThanOrEqual,
250 SmiLessThanOrEqual)
251 PARAMETER_BINOP(IntPtrOrSmiGreaterThan, IntPtrGreaterThan, SmiGreaterThan)
252#undef PARAMETER_BINOP
253
254#define PARAMETER_BINOP(OpName, UintPtrOpName, SmiOpName) \
255 TNode<BoolT> OpName(TNode<Smi> a, TNode<Smi> b) { return SmiOpName(a, b); } \
256 TNode<BoolT> OpName(TNode<IntPtrT> a, TNode<IntPtrT> b) { \
257 return UintPtrOpName(Unsigned(a), Unsigned(b)); \
258 } \
259 TNode<BoolT> OpName(TNode<UintPtrT> a, TNode<UintPtrT> b) { \
260 return UintPtrOpName(a, b); \
261 } \
262 TNode<BoolT> OpName(TNode<RawPtrT> a, TNode<RawPtrT> b) { \
263 return UintPtrOpName(a, b); \
264 }
265 // TODO(v8:9708): Define BInt operations once all uses are ported.
266 PARAMETER_BINOP(UintPtrOrSmiEqual, WordEqual, SmiEqual)
267 PARAMETER_BINOP(UintPtrOrSmiNotEqual, WordNotEqual, SmiNotEqual)
268 PARAMETER_BINOP(UintPtrOrSmiLessThan, UintPtrLessThan, SmiBelow)
269 PARAMETER_BINOP(UintPtrOrSmiLessThanOrEqual, UintPtrLessThanOrEqual,
270 SmiBelowOrEqual)
271 PARAMETER_BINOP(UintPtrOrSmiGreaterThan, UintPtrGreaterThan, SmiAbove)
272 PARAMETER_BINOP(UintPtrOrSmiGreaterThanOrEqual, UintPtrGreaterThanOrEqual,
273 SmiAboveOrEqual)
274#undef PARAMETER_BINOP

276 uintptr_t ConstexprUintPtrShl(uintptr_t a, int32_t b) { return a << b; }
277 uintptr_t ConstexprUintPtrShr(uintptr_t a, int32_t b) { return a >> b; }
278 intptr_t ConstexprIntPtrAdd(intptr_t a, intptr_t b) { return a + b; }
279 uintptr_t ConstexprUintPtrAdd(uintptr_t a, uintptr_t b) { return a + b; }
280 intptr_t ConstexprWordNot(intptr_t a) { return ~a; }
281 uintptr_t ConstexprWordNot(uintptr_t a) { return ~a; }

283 TNode<BoolT> TaggedEqual(TNode<AnyTaggedT> a, TNode<AnyTaggedT> b) {
284 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
285 return Word32Equal(ReinterpretCast<Word32T>(a),
286 ReinterpretCast<Word32T>(b));
287 } else {
288 return WordEqual(ReinterpretCast<WordT>(a), ReinterpretCast<WordT>(b));
289 }
290 }
291
292 TNode<BoolT> TaggedNotEqual(TNode<AnyTaggedT> a, TNode<AnyTaggedT> b) {
293 return Word32BinaryNot(TaggedEqual(a, b));
294 }

298 TNode<IntPtrT> StackAlignmentInBytes() {
299 // This node makes the graph platform-specific. To make sure that the graph
300 // structure is still platform independent, UniqueIntPtrConstants are used
301 // here.
302#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64
303 return UniqueIntPtrConstant(16);
304#else
305 return UniqueIntPtrConstant(kSystemPointerSize);
306#endif
307 }

386 // Smi operations.
387#define SMI_ARITHMETIC_BINOP(SmiOpName, IntPtrOpName, Int32OpName) \
388 TNode<Smi> SmiOpName(TNode<Smi> a, TNode<Smi> b) { \
389 if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) { \
390 return BitcastWordToTaggedSigned( \
391 IntPtrOpName(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a), \
392 BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(b))); \
393 } else { \
394 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits()); \
395 return BitcastWordToTaggedSigned(ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(Int32OpName( \
396 TruncateIntPtrToInt32(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a)), \
397 TruncateIntPtrToInt32(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(b))))); \
398 } \
399 }
400 SMI_ARITHMETIC_BINOP(SmiAdd, IntPtrAdd, Int32Add)
401 SMI_ARITHMETIC_BINOP(SmiSub, IntPtrSub, Int32Sub)
402 SMI_ARITHMETIC_BINOP(SmiAnd, WordAnd, Word32And)
403 SMI_ARITHMETIC_BINOP(SmiOr, WordOr, Word32Or)
404 SMI_ARITHMETIC_BINOP(SmiXor, WordXor, Word32Xor)
405#undef SMI_ARITHMETIC_BINOP

423 TNode<Smi> UnsignedSmiShl(TNode<Smi> a, int shift) {
424 if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
425 return BitcastWordToTaggedSigned(
426 WordShl(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a), shift));
427 } else {
428 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
429 return BitcastWordToTaggedSigned(ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(Word32Shl(
430 TruncateIntPtrToInt32(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a)),
431 Int32Constant(shift))));
432 }
433 }
434
435 TNode<Smi> SmiShl(TNode<Smi> a, int shift) {
436 TNode<Smi> result = UnsignedSmiShl(a, shift);
437 // Smi shift have different result to int32 shift when the inputs are not
438 // strictly limited. The CSA_DCHECK is to ensure valid inputs.
439 CSA_DCHECK(
440 this, TaggedEqual(result, BitwiseOp(SmiToInt32(a), Int32Constant(shift),
441 Operation::kShiftLeft)));
442 return result;
443 }
444
445 TNode<Smi> SmiShr(TNode<Smi> a, int shift) {
446 TNode<Smi> result;
447 if (kTaggedSize == kInt64Size) {
448 result = BitcastWordToTaggedSigned(
449 WordAnd(WordShr(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a), shift),
450 BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(SmiConstant(-1))));
451 } else {
452 // For pointer compressed Smis, we want to make sure that we truncate to
453 // int32 before shifting, to avoid the values of the top 32-bits from
454 // leaking into the sign bit of the smi.
455 result = BitcastWordToTaggedSigned(WordAnd(
456 ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(Word32Shr(
457 TruncateWordToInt32(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a)),
458 shift)),
459 BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(SmiConstant(-1))));
460 }
461 // Smi shift have different result to int32 shift when the inputs are not
462 // strictly limited. The CSA_DCHECK is to ensure valid inputs.
463 CSA_DCHECK(
464 this, TaggedEqual(result, BitwiseOp(SmiToInt32(a), Int32Constant(shift),
465 Operation::kShiftRightLogical)));
466 return result;
467 }
468
469 TNode<Smi> SmiSar(TNode<Smi> a, int shift) {
470 // The number of shift bits is |shift % 64| for 64-bits value and |shift %
471 // 32| for 32-bits value. The DCHECK is to ensure valid inputs.
472 DCHECK_LT(shift, 32);
473 if (kTaggedSize == kInt64Size) {
474 return BitcastWordToTaggedSigned(
475 WordAnd(WordSar(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a), shift),
476 BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(SmiConstant(-1))));
477 } else {
478 // For pointer compressed Smis, we want to make sure that we truncate to
479 // int32 before shifting, to avoid the values of the top 32-bits from
480 // changing the sign bit of the smi.
481 return BitcastWordToTaggedSigned(WordAnd(
482 ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(Word32Sar(
483 TruncateWordToInt32(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a)),
484 shift)),
485 BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(SmiConstant(-1))));
486 }
487 }
488
489 TNode<Smi> WordOrSmiShr(TNode<Smi> a, int shift) { return SmiShr(a, shift); }
490
491 TNode<IntPtrT> WordOrSmiShr(TNode<IntPtrT> a, int shift) {
492 return WordShr(a, shift);
493 }

495#define SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiOpName, IntPtrOpName, Int32OpName) \
496 TNode<BoolT> SmiOpName(TNode<Smi> a, TNode<Smi> b) { \
497 if (kTaggedSize == kInt64Size) { \
498 return IntPtrOpName(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a), \
499 BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(b)); \
500 } else { \
501 DCHECK_EQ(kTaggedSize, kInt32Size); \
502 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits()); \
503 return Int32OpName( \
504 TruncateIntPtrToInt32(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a)), \
505 TruncateIntPtrToInt32(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(b))); \
506 } \
507 }
508 SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiEqual, WordEqual, Word32Equal)
509 SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiNotEqual, WordNotEqual, Word32NotEqual)
510 SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiAbove, UintPtrGreaterThan, Uint32GreaterThan)
511 SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiAboveOrEqual, UintPtrGreaterThanOrEqual,
512 Uint32GreaterThanOrEqual)
513 SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiBelow, UintPtrLessThan, Uint32LessThan)
514 SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiBelowOrEqual, UintPtrLessThanOrEqual,
515 Uint32LessThanOrEqual)
516 SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiLessThan, IntPtrLessThan, Int32LessThan)
517 SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiLessThanOrEqual, IntPtrLessThanOrEqual,
518 Int32LessThanOrEqual)
519 SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiGreaterThan, IntPtrGreaterThan, Int32GreaterThan)
520 SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiGreaterThanOrEqual, IntPtrGreaterThanOrEqual,
521 Int32GreaterThanOrEqual)
522#undef SMI_COMPARISON_OP
523 TNode<Smi> SmiMax(TNode<Smi> a, TNode<Smi> b);
524 TNode<Smi> SmiMin(TNode<Smi> a, TNode<Smi> b);
525 // Computes a % b for Smi inputs a and b; result is not necessarily a Smi.
526 TNode<Number> SmiMod(TNode<Smi> a, TNode<Smi> b);
527 // Computes a * b for Smi inputs a and b; result is not necessarily a Smi.
528 TNode<Number> SmiMul(TNode<Smi> a, TNode<Smi> b);
529 // Tries to compute dividend / divisor for Smi inputs; branching to bailout
530 // if the division needs to be performed as a floating point operation.
531 TNode<Smi> TrySmiDiv(TNode<Smi> dividend, TNode<Smi> divisor, Label* bailout);

534 // compared lexicographically. Returns:

536 // 0 iff x == y.
537 // 1 iff x > y.
538 TNode<Smi> SmiLexicographicCompare(TNode<Smi> x, TNode<Smi> y);

704
705 template <typename T>
706 TNode<T> Select(TNode<BoolT> condition, const NodeGenerator<T>& true_body,
707 const NodeGenerator<T>& false_body,
708 BranchHint branch_hint = BranchHint::kNone) {
709 TVARIABLE(T, value);
710 Label vtrue(this), vfalse(this), end(this);
711 Branch(condition, &vtrue, &vfalse, branch_hint);
712
713 BIND(&vtrue);
714 {
715 value = true_body();
716 Goto(&end);
717 }
718 BIND(&vfalse);
719 {
720 value = false_body();
721 Goto(&end);
722 }
723
724 BIND(&end);
725 return value.value();
726 }
727
728 template <class A>
729 TNode<A> SelectConstant(TNode<BoolT> condition, TNode<A> true_value,
730 TNode<A> false_value) {
731 return Select<A>(
732 condition, [=] { return true_value; }, [=] { return false_value; });
733 }
734
735 TNode<Int32T> SelectInt32Constant(TNode<BoolT> condition, int true_value,
736 int false_value);
737 TNode<IntPtrT> SelectIntPtrConstant(TNode<BoolT> condition, int true_value,
738 int false_value);
739 TNode<Boolean> SelectBooleanConstant(TNode<BoolT> condition);
740 TNode<Smi> SelectSmiConstant(TNode<BoolT> condition, Tagged<Smi> true_value,
741 Tagged<Smi> false_value);
742 TNode<Smi> SelectSmiConstant(TNode<BoolT> condition, int true_value,
743 Tagged<Smi> false_value) {
744 return SelectSmiConstant(condition, Smi::FromInt(true_value), false_value);
745 }

747 int false_value) {

749 }

753 Smi::FromInt(false_value));
754 }

780 // Check if lower_limit <= value <= higher_limit.
781 template <typename U>
782 TNode<BoolT> IsInRange(TNode<Word32T> value, U lower_limit, U higher_limit) {
783 DCHECK_LE(lower_limit, higher_limit);
784 static_assert(sizeof(U) <= kInt32Size);
785 if (lower_limit == 0) {
786 return Uint32LessThanOrEqual(value, Int32Constant(higher_limit));
787 }
788 return Uint32LessThanOrEqual(Int32Sub(value, Int32Constant(lower_limit)),
789 Int32Constant(higher_limit - lower_limit));
790 }
791
792 TNode<BoolT> IsInRange(TNode<UintPtrT> value, TNode<UintPtrT> lower_limit,
793 TNode<UintPtrT> higher_limit) {
794 CSA_DCHECK(this, UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(lower_limit, higher_limit));
795 return UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(UintPtrSub(value, lower_limit),
796 UintPtrSub(higher_limit, lower_limit));
797 }
798
799 TNode<BoolT> IsInRange(TNode<WordT> value, intptr_t lower_limit,
800 intptr_t higher_limit) {
801 DCHECK_LE(lower_limit, higher_limit);
802 if (lower_limit == 0) {
803 return UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(value, IntPtrConstant(higher_limit));
804 }
805 return UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(IntPtrSub(value, IntPtrConstant(lower_limit)),
806 IntPtrConstant(higher_limit - lower_limit));
807 }

1051 // Returns WasmImportData or WasmTrustedInstanceData.
1052 TNode<TrustedObject> LoadImplicitArgFromWasmInternalFunction(
1053 TNode<WasmInternalFunction> object) {
1054 TNode<Object> obj = LoadProtectedPointerField(
1055 object, WasmInternalFunction::kProtectedImplicitArgOffset);
1056 CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedIsNotSmi(obj));
1057 TNode<HeapObject> implicit_arg = CAST(obj);
1058 CSA_DCHECK(
1059 this,
1060 Word32Or(HasInstanceType(implicit_arg, WASM_TRUSTED_INSTANCE_DATA_TYPE),
1061 HasInstanceType(implicit_arg, WASM_IMPORT_DATA_TYPE)));
1062 return CAST(implicit_arg);

1145 // Load a field from an object on the heap.
1146 template <typename T>
1147 TNode<T> LoadObjectField(TNode<HeapObject> object, int offset) {
1148 MachineType machine_type = MachineTypeOf<T>::value;
1149 TNode<IntPtrT> raw_offset = IntPtrConstant(offset - kHeapObjectTag);
1150 if constexpr (is_subtype_v<T, UntaggedT>) {
1151 // Load an untagged field.
1152 return UncheckedCast<T>(LoadFromObject(machine_type, object, raw_offset));
1153 } else {
1154 static_assert(is_subtype_v<T, Object>);
1155 // Load a tagged field.
1156 if constexpr (is_subtype_v<T, Map>) {
1157 // If this is potentially loading a map, we need to check the offset.
1158 if (offset == HeapObject::kMapOffset) {
1159 machine_type = MachineType::MapInHeader();
1160 }
1161 }
1162 return CAST(LoadFromObject(machine_type, object, raw_offset));
1163 }
1164 }
1165 TNode<Object> LoadObjectField(TNode<HeapObject> object, int offset) {
1166 return UncheckedCast<Object>(
1167 LoadFromObject(MachineType::AnyTagged(), object,
1168 IntPtrConstant(offset - kHeapObjectTag)));
1169 }
1170 TNode<Object> LoadObjectField(TNode<HeapObject> object,
1171 TNode<IntPtrT> offset) {
1172 return UncheckedCast<Object>(
1173 LoadFromObject(MachineType::AnyTagged(), object,
1174 IntPtrSub(offset, IntPtrConstant(kHeapObjectTag))));
1175 }
1176 template <class T>
1177 TNode<T> LoadObjectField(TNode<HeapObject> object, TNode<IntPtrT> offset)
1178 requires std::is_convertible<TNode<T>, TNode<UntaggedT>>::value
1179 {
1180 return UncheckedCast<T>(
1181 LoadFromObject(MachineTypeOf<T>::value, object,
1182 IntPtrSub(offset, IntPtrConstant(kHeapObjectTag))));
1183 }
1184 // Load a positive SMI field and untag it.
1185 TNode<IntPtrT> LoadAndUntagPositiveSmiObjectField(TNode<HeapObject> object,
1186 int offset);
1187 // Load a SMI field, untag it, and convert to Word32.
1188 TNode<Int32T> LoadAndUntagToWord32ObjectField(TNode<HeapObject> object,
1189 int offset);
1190
1191 TNode<MaybeObject> LoadMaybeWeakObjectField(TNode<HeapObject> object,
1192 int offset) {
1193 return UncheckedCast<MaybeObject>(LoadObjectField(object, offset));
1194 }

1196 TNode<Object> LoadConstructorOrBackPointer(TNode<Map> map) {
1197 return LoadObjectField(map,
1198 Map::kConstructorOrBackPointerOrNativeContextOffset);

1204
1205 // Reference is the CSA-equivalent of a Torque reference value, representing
1206 // an inner pointer into a HeapObject.
1207 //
1208 // The object can be a HeapObject or an all-zero bitpattern. The latter is
1209 // used for off-heap data, in which case the offset holds the actual address
1210 // and the data must be untagged (i.e. accessed via the Load-/StoreReference
1211 // overloads for TNode<UntaggedT>-convertible types below).
1212 //
1213 // TODO(gsps): Remove in favor of flattened {Load,Store}Reference interface.
1214 struct Reference {
1215 TNode<Object> object;
1216 TNode<IntPtrT> offset;
1217
1218 std::tuple<TNode<Object>, TNode<IntPtrT>> Flatten() const {
1219 return std::make_tuple(object, offset);
1220 }
1221 };
1222
1223 template <class T>
1224 TNode<T> LoadReference(Reference reference)
1225 requires std::is_convertible<TNode<T>, TNode<Object>>::value
1226 {
1227 if (IsMapOffsetConstant(reference.offset)) {
1228 TNode<Map> map = LoadMap(CAST(reference.object));
1229 DCHECK((std::is_base_of<T, Map>::value));
1230 return ReinterpretCast<T>(map);
1231 }
1232
1233 TNode<IntPtrT> offset =
1234 IntPtrSub(reference.offset, IntPtrConstant(kHeapObjectTag));
1235 CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedIsNotSmi(reference.object));
1236 return CAST(
1237 LoadFromObject(MachineTypeOf<T>::value, reference.object, offset));
1238 }
1239 template <class T>
1240 TNode<T> LoadReference(Reference reference)
1241 requires(std::is_convertible<TNode<T>, TNode<UntaggedT>>::value ||
1242 std::is_same<T, MaybeObject>::value)
1243 {
1244 DCHECK(!IsMapOffsetConstant(reference.offset));
1245 TNode<IntPtrT> offset =
1246 IntPtrSub(reference.offset, IntPtrConstant(kHeapObjectTag));
1247 return UncheckedCast<T>(
1248 LoadFromObject(MachineTypeOf<T>::value, reference.object, offset));
1249 }
1250 template <class T>
1251 void StoreReference(Reference reference, TNode<T> value)
1252 requires(std::is_convertible<TNode<T>, TNode<Object>>::value ||
1253 std::is_same<T, MaybeObject>::value)
1254 {
1255 if (IsMapOffsetConstant(reference.offset)) {
1256 DCHECK((std::is_base_of<T, Map>::value));
1257 return StoreMap(CAST(reference.object), ReinterpretCast<Map>(value));
1258 }
1259 MachineRepresentation rep = MachineRepresentationOf<T>::value;
1260 StoreToObjectWriteBarrier write_barrier = StoreToObjectWriteBarrier::kFull;
1261 if (std::is_same<T, Smi>::value) {
1262 write_barrier = StoreToObjectWriteBarrier::kNone;
1263 } else if (std::is_same<T, Map>::value) {
1264 write_barrier = StoreToObjectWriteBarrier::kMap;
1265 }
1266 TNode<IntPtrT> offset =
1267 IntPtrSub(reference.offset, IntPtrConstant(kHeapObjectTag));
1268 CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedIsNotSmi(reference.object));
1269 StoreToObject(rep, reference.object, offset, value, write_barrier);
1270 }
1271 template <class T>
1272 void StoreReference(Reference reference, TNode<T> value)
1273 requires std::is_convertible<TNode<T>, TNode<UntaggedT>>::value
1274 {
1275 DCHECK(!IsMapOffsetConstant(reference.offset));
1276 TNode<IntPtrT> offset =
1277 IntPtrSub(reference.offset, IntPtrConstant(kHeapObjectTag));
1278 StoreToObject(MachineRepresentationOf<T>::value, reference.object, offset,
1279 value, StoreToObjectWriteBarrier::kNone);
1280 }
1281
1282 TNode<RawPtrT> GCUnsafeReferenceToRawPtr(TNode<Object> object,
1283 TNode<IntPtrT> offset) {
1284 return ReinterpretCast<RawPtrT>(
1285 IntPtrAdd(BitcastTaggedToWord(object),
1286 IntPtrSub(offset, IntPtrConstant(kHeapObjectTag))));
1287 }

1577 TNode<BoolT> IsDoubleHole(TNode<Object> base, TNode<IntPtrT> offset);
1578 // Load Float64 value by |base| + |offset| address. If the value is a double
1579 // hole then jump to |if_hole|. If |machine_type| is None then only the hole
1580 // check is generated.

1692 // Store to an indirect pointer field. This involves loading the index for
1693 // the pointer table entry owned by the pointed-to object (which points back
1694 // to it) and storing that into the specified field.
1695 // Stores that may require a write barrier also need to know the indirect
1696 // pointer tag for the field. Otherwise, it is not needed
1697 void StoreIndirectPointerField(TNode<HeapObject> object, int offset,
1698 IndirectPointerTag tag,
1699 TNode<ExposedTrustedObject> value);
1700 void StoreIndirectPointerFieldNoWriteBarrier(
1701 TNode<HeapObject> object, int offset, IndirectPointerTag tag,
1702 TNode<ExposedTrustedObject> value);
1703
1704 // Store a trusted pointer field.
1705 // When the sandbox is enabled, these are indirect pointers using the trusted
1706 // pointer table. Otherwise they are regular tagged fields.
1707 void StoreTrustedPointerField(TNode<HeapObject> object, int offset,
1708 IndirectPointerTag tag,
1709 TNode<ExposedTrustedObject> value);
1710 void StoreTrustedPointerFieldNoWriteBarrier(
1711 TNode<HeapObject> object, int offset, IndirectPointerTag tag,
1712 TNode<ExposedTrustedObject> value);
1713
1714 void ClearTrustedPointerField(TNode<HeapObject> object, int offset);
1715
1716 // Store a code pointer field.
1717 // These are special versions of trusted pointers that, when the sandbox is
1718 // enabled, reference code objects through the code pointer table.
1719 void StoreCodePointerField(TNode<HeapObject> object, int offset,
1720 TNode<Code> value) {
1721 StoreTrustedPointerField(object, offset, kCodeIndirectPointerTag, value);
1722 }
1723 void StoreCodePointerFieldNoWriteBarrier(TNode<HeapObject> object, int offset,
1724 TNode<Code> value) {
1725 StoreTrustedPointerFieldNoWriteBarrier(object, offset,
1726 kCodeIndirectPointerTag, value);
1727 }
1728
1729 template <class T>
1730 void StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(TNode<HeapObject> object,
1731 TNode<IntPtrT> offset, TNode<T> value) {
1732 int const_offset;
1733 if (TryToInt32Constant(offset, &const_offset)) {
1734 return StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier<T>(object, const_offset, value);
1735 }
1736 StoreNoWriteBarrier(MachineRepresentationOf<T>::value, object,
1737 IntPtrSub(offset, IntPtrConstant(kHeapObjectTag)),
1738 value);
1739 }
1740 template <class T>
1741 void StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(TNode<HeapObject> object, int offset,
1742 TNode<T> value) {
1743 if (CanBeTaggedPointer(MachineRepresentationOf<T>::value)) {
1744 OptimizedStoreFieldAssertNoWriteBarrier(MachineRepresentationOf<T>::value,
1745 object, offset, value);
1746 } else {
1747 OptimizedStoreFieldUnsafeNoWriteBarrier(MachineRepresentationOf<T>::value,
1748 object, offset, value);
1749 }
1750 }
1751
1752 void UnsafeStoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(TNode<HeapObject> object,
1753 int offset, TNode<Object> value);
1754

1756 void StoreMap(TNode<HeapObject> object, TNode<Map> map);
1757 void StoreMapNoWriteBarrier(TNode<HeapObject> object,
1758 RootIndex map_root_index);
1759 void StoreMapNoWriteBarrier(TNode<HeapObject> object, TNode<Map> map);
1760 void StoreObjectFieldRoot(TNode<HeapObject> object, int offset,
1761 RootIndex root);

1763 // Store an array element to a FixedArray.
1764 void StoreFixedArrayElement(
1765 TNode<FixedArray> object, int index, TNode<Object> value,
1766 WriteBarrierMode barrier_mode = UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER,
1767 CheckBounds check_bounds = CheckBounds::kAlways) {
1768 return StoreFixedArrayElement(object, IntPtrConstant(index), value,
1769 barrier_mode, 0, check_bounds);
1770 }
1771
1772 void StoreFixedArrayElement(TNode<FixedArray> object, int index,
1773 TNode<Smi> value,
1774 CheckBounds check_bounds = CheckBounds::kAlways) {
1775 return StoreFixedArrayElement(object, IntPtrConstant(index),
1776 TNode<Object>{value},
1777 UNSAFE_SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER, 0, check_bounds);
1778 }
1779
1780 template <typename TIndex>
1781 void StoreFixedArrayElement(
1782 TNode<FixedArray> array, TNode<TIndex> index, TNode<Object> value,
1783 WriteBarrierMode barrier_mode = UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER,
1784 int additional_offset = 0,
1785 CheckBounds check_bounds = CheckBounds::kAlways) {
1786 // TODO(v8:9708): Do we want to keep both IntPtrT and UintPtrT variants?
1787 static_assert(std::is_same<TIndex, Smi>::value ||
1788 std::is_same<TIndex, UintPtrT>::value ||
1789 std::is_same<TIndex, IntPtrT>::value,
1790 "Only Smi, UintPtrT or IntPtrT index is allowed");
1791 if (NeedsBoundsCheck(check_bounds)) {
1792 FixedArrayBoundsCheck(array, index, additional_offset);
1793 }
1794 StoreFixedArrayOrPropertyArrayElement(array, index, value, barrier_mode,
1795 additional_offset);
1796 }
1797
1798 template <typename TIndex>
1799 void StoreFixedArrayElement(TNode<FixedArray> array, TNode<TIndex> index,
1800 TNode<Smi> value, int additional_offset = 0) {
1801 static_assert(std::is_same<TIndex, Smi>::value ||
1802 std::is_same<TIndex, IntPtrT>::value,
1803 "Only Smi or IntPtrT indeces is allowed");
1804 StoreFixedArrayElement(array, index, TNode<Object>{value},
1805 UNSAFE_SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER, additional_offset);
1806 }
1807
1808 // These don't emit a bounds-check. As part of the security-performance
1809 // tradeoff, only use it if it is performance critical.
1810 void UnsafeStoreFixedArrayElement(
1811 TNode<FixedArray> object, int index, TNode<Object> value,
1812 WriteBarrierMode barrier_mode = UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER) {
1813 return StoreFixedArrayElement(object, IntPtrConstant(index), value,
1814 barrier_mode, 0, CheckBounds::kDebugOnly);
1815 }
1816 template <typename Array>
1817 void UnsafeStoreArrayElement(
1818 TNode<Array> object, int index,
1819 TNode<typename Array::Shape::ElementT> value,
1820 WriteBarrierMode barrier_mode = UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER) {
1821 DCHECK(barrier_mode == SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER ||
1822 barrier_mode == UNSAFE_SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER ||
1823 barrier_mode == UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER);
1824 // TODO(jgruber): This is just a barebones implementation taken from
1825 // StoreFixedArrayOrPropertyArrayElement. We can make it more robust and
1826 // generic if needed.
1827 int offset = Array::OffsetOfElementAt(index);
1828 if (barrier_mode == UNSAFE_SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER) {
1829 UnsafeStoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(object, offset, value);
1830 } else if (barrier_mode == SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER) {
1831 StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(object, offset, value);
1832 } else if (barrier_mode == UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER) {
1833 StoreObjectField(object, offset, value);
1834 } else {
1835 UNREACHABLE();
1836 }
1837 }
1838 template <typename Array>
1839 void UnsafeStoreArrayElement(
1840 TNode<Array> object, TNode<Smi> index,
1841 TNode<typename Array::Shape::ElementT> value,
1842 WriteBarrierMode barrier_mode = UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER) {
1843 DCHECK(barrier_mode == SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER ||
1844 barrier_mode == UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER);
1845 // TODO(jgruber): This is just a barebones implementation taken from
1846 // StoreFixedArrayOrPropertyArrayElement. We can make it more robust and
1847 // generic if needed.
1848 TNode<IntPtrT> offset = ElementOffsetFromIndex(index, PACKED_ELEMENTS,
1849 OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(Array));
1850 if (barrier_mode == SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER) {
1851 StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(object, offset, value);
1852 } else if (barrier_mode == UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER) {
1853 StoreObjectField(object, offset, value);
1854 } else {
1855 UNREACHABLE();
1856 }
1857 }
1858
1859 void UnsafeStoreFixedArrayElement(TNode<FixedArray> object, int index,
1860 TNode<Smi> value) {
1861 return StoreFixedArrayElement(object, IntPtrConstant(index), value,
1862 UNSAFE_SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER, 0,
1863 CheckBounds::kDebugOnly);
1864 }

2097 enum class HoleConversionMode { kDontConvert, kConvertToUndefined };
2098 // Clone a fast JSArray |array| into a new fast JSArray.
2099 // |convert_holes| tells the function to convert holes into undefined or not.
2100 // If |convert_holes| is set to kConvertToUndefined, but the function did not
2101 // find any hole in |array|, the resulting array will have the same elements
2102 // kind as |array|. If the function did find a hole, it will convert holes in
2103 // |array| to undefined in the resulting array, who will now have
2104 // PACKED_ELEMENTS kind.
2105 // If |convert_holes| is set kDontConvert, holes are also copied to the
2106 // resulting array, who will have the same elements kind as |array|. The
2107 // function generates significantly less code in this case.
2108 TNode<JSArray> CloneFastJSArray(
2109 TNode<Context> context, TNode<JSArray> array,
2110 std::optional<TNode<AllocationSite>> allocation_site = std::nullopt,
2111 HoleConversionMode convert_holes = HoleConversionMode::kDontConvert);
2112
2113 TNode<JSArray> ExtractFastJSArray(TNode<Context> context,
2114 TNode<JSArray> array, TNode<BInt> begin,
2115 TNode<BInt> count);

2366 enum class ExtractFixedArrayFlag {
2367 kFixedArrays = 1,
2368 kFixedDoubleArrays = 2,
2369 kDontCopyCOW = 4,
2370 kAllFixedArrays = kFixedArrays | kFixedDoubleArrays,
2371 kAllFixedArraysDontCopyCOW = kAllFixedArrays | kDontCopyCOW
2372 };
2373
2374 using ExtractFixedArrayFlags = base::Flags<ExtractFixedArrayFlag>;
2375
2376 // Copy a portion of an existing FixedArray or FixedDoubleArray into a new
2377 // array, including special appropriate handling for empty arrays and COW
2378 // arrays. The result array will be of the same type as the original array.
2379 //
2380 // * |source| is either a FixedArray or FixedDoubleArray from which to copy
2381 // elements.
2382 // * |first| is the starting element index to copy from, if nullptr is passed
2383 // then index zero is used by default.
2384 // * |count| is the number of elements to copy out of the source array
2385 // starting from and including the element indexed by |start|. If |count| is
2386 // nullptr, then all of the elements from |start| to the end of |source| are
2387 // copied.
2388 // * |capacity| determines the size of the allocated result array, with
2389 // |capacity| >= |count|. If |capacity| is nullptr, then |count| is used as
2390 // the destination array's capacity.
2391 // * |extract_flags| determines whether FixedArrays, FixedDoubleArrays or both
2392 // are detected and copied. Although it's always correct to pass
2393 // kAllFixedArrays, the generated code is more compact and efficient if the
2394 // caller can specify whether only FixedArrays or FixedDoubleArrays will be
2395 // passed as the |source| parameter.
2396 // * |parameter_mode| determines the parameter mode of |first|, |count| and
2397 // |capacity|.
2398 // * If |var_holes_converted| is given, any holes will be converted to
2399 // undefined and the variable will be set according to whether or not there
2400 // were any hole.
2401 // * If |source_elements_kind| is given, the function will try to use the
2402 // runtime elements kind of source to make copy faster. More specifically, it
2403 // can skip write barriers.
2404 template <typename TIndex>
2405 TNode<FixedArrayBase> ExtractFixedArray(
2406 TNode<FixedArrayBase> source, std::optional<TNode<TIndex>> first,
2407 std::optional<TNode<TIndex>> count = std::nullopt,
2408 std::optional<TNode<TIndex>> capacity = std::nullopt,
2409 ExtractFixedArrayFlags extract_flags =
2410 ExtractFixedArrayFlag::kAllFixedArrays,
2411 TVariable<BoolT>* var_holes_converted = nullptr,
2412 std::optional<TNode<Int32T>> source_elements_kind = std::nullopt);
2413
2414 // Copy a portion of an existing FixedArray or FixedDoubleArray into a new
2415 // FixedArray, including special appropriate handling for COW arrays.
2416 // * |source| is either a FixedArray or FixedDoubleArray from which to copy
2417 // elements. |source| is assumed to be non-empty.
2418 // * |first| is the starting element index to copy from.
2419 // * |count| is the number of elements to copy out of the source array
2420 // starting from and including the element indexed by |start|.
2421 // * |capacity| determines the size of the allocated result array, with
2422 // |capacity| >= |count|.
2423 // * |source_map| is the map of the |source|.
2424 // * |from_kind| is the elements kind that is consistent with |source| being
2425 // a FixedArray or FixedDoubleArray. This function only cares about double vs.
2426 // non-double, so as to distinguish FixedDoubleArray vs. FixedArray. It does
2427 // not care about holeyness. For example, when |source| is a FixedArray,
2428 // PACKED/HOLEY_ELEMENTS can be used, but not PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS.
2429 // * |allocation_flags| and |extract_flags| influence how the target
2430 // FixedArray is allocated.
2431 // * |convert_holes| is used to signify that the target array should use
2432 // undefined in places of holes.
2433 // * If |convert_holes| is true and |var_holes_converted| not nullptr, then
2434 // |var_holes_converted| is used to signal whether any holes were found and
2435 // converted. The caller should use this information to decide which map is
2436 // compatible with the result array. For example, if the input was of
2437 // HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS kind, and a conversion took place, the result will be
2438 // compatible only with HOLEY_ELEMENTS and PACKED_ELEMENTS.
2439 template <typename TIndex>
2440 TNode<FixedArray> ExtractToFixedArray(
2441 TNode<FixedArrayBase> source, TNode<TIndex> first, TNode<TIndex> count,
2442 TNode<TIndex> capacity, TNode<Map> source_map, ElementsKind from_kind,
2443 AllocationFlags allocation_flags, ExtractFixedArrayFlags extract_flags,
2444 HoleConversionMode convert_holes,
2445 TVariable<BoolT>* var_holes_converted = nullptr,
2446 std::optional<TNode<Int32T>> source_runtime_kind = std::nullopt);
2447
2448 // Attempt to copy a FixedDoubleArray to another FixedDoubleArray. In the case
2449 // where the source array has a hole, produce a FixedArray instead where holes
2450 // are replaced with undefined.
2451 // * |source| is a FixedDoubleArray from which to copy elements.
2452 // * |first| is the starting element index to copy from.
2453 // * |count| is the number of elements to copy out of the source array
2454 // starting from and including the element indexed by |start|.
2455 // * |capacity| determines the size of the allocated result array, with
2456 // |capacity| >= |count|.
2457 // * |source_map| is the map of |source|. It will be used as the map of the
2458 // target array if the target can stay a FixedDoubleArray. Otherwise if the
2459 // target array needs to be a FixedArray, the FixedArrayMap will be used.
2460 // * |var_holes_converted| is used to signal whether a FixedAray
2461 // is produced or not.
2462 // * |allocation_flags| and |extract_flags| influence how the target array is
2463 // allocated.
2464 template <typename TIndex>
2465 TNode<FixedArrayBase> ExtractFixedDoubleArrayFillingHoles(
2466 TNode<FixedArrayBase> source, TNode<TIndex> first, TNode<TIndex> count,
2467 TNode<TIndex> capacity, TNode<Map> source_map,
2468 TVariable<BoolT>* var_holes_converted, AllocationFlags allocation_flags,
2469 ExtractFixedArrayFlags extract_flags);
2470
2471 // Copy the entire contents of a FixedArray or FixedDoubleArray to a new
2472 // array, including special appropriate handling for empty arrays and COW
2473 // arrays.
2474 //
2475 // * |source| is either a FixedArray or FixedDoubleArray from which to copy
2476 // elements.
2477 // * |extract_flags| determines whether FixedArrays, FixedDoubleArrays or both
2478 // are detected and copied. Although it's always correct to pass
2479 // kAllFixedArrays, the generated code is more compact and efficient if the
2480 // caller can specify whether only FixedArrays or FixedDoubleArrays will be
2481 // passed as the |source| parameter.
2482 TNode<FixedArrayBase> CloneFixedArray(
2483 TNode<FixedArrayBase> source,
2484 ExtractFixedArrayFlags flags =
2485 ExtractFixedArrayFlag::kAllFixedArraysDontCopyCOW);

2852 TNode<BoolT> LoadRuntimeFlag(ExternalReference address_of_flag) {
2853 TNode<Word32T> flag_value = UncheckedCast<Word32T>(
2854 Load(MachineType::Uint8(), ExternalConstant(address_of_flag)));
2855 return Word32NotEqual(Word32And(flag_value, Int32Constant(0xFF)),
2856 Int32Constant(0));
2857 }

3031 // Returns a node that contains a decoded (unsigned!) value of a bit
3032 // field |BitField| in |word32|. Returns result as an uint32 node.
3033 template <typename BitField>
3034 TNode<Uint32T> DecodeWord32(TNode<Word32T> word32) {

3053 // field |BitField| in |word|. Returns result as an uint32 node.

3057 TruncateIntPtrToInt32(Signed(DecodeWord<BitField>(word))));

3127 Int32Constant(0));

3141
3142 // Returns true if the bit field |BitField| in |word32| is equal to a given
3143 // constant |value|. Avoids a shift compared to using DecodeWord32.
3144 template <typename BitField>
3145 TNode<BoolT> IsEqualInWord32(TNode<Word32T> word32,
3146 typename BitField::FieldType value) {
3147 TNode<Word32T> masked_word32 =
3148 Word32And(word32, Int32Constant(BitField::kMask));
3149 return Word32Equal(masked_word32, Int32Constant(BitField::encode(value)));
3150 }
3151
3152 // Checks if two values of non-overlapping bitfields are both set.
3153 template <typename BitField1, typename BitField2>
3154 TNode<BoolT> IsBothEqualInWord32(TNode<Word32T> word32,
3155 typename BitField1::FieldType value1,
3156 typename BitField2::FieldType value2) {
3157 static_assert((BitField1::kMask & BitField2::kMask) == 0);
3158 TNode<Word32T> combined_masked_word32 =
3159 Word32And(word32, Int32Constant(BitField1::kMask | BitField2::kMask));
3160 TNode<Int32T> combined_value =
3161 Int32Constant(BitField1::encode(value1) | BitField2::encode(value2));
3162 return Word32Equal(combined_masked_word32, combined_value);
3163 }
3164
3165 // Returns true if the bit field |BitField| in |word32| is not equal to a
3166 // given constant |value|. Avoids a shift compared to using DecodeWord32.
3167 template <typename BitField>
3168 TNode<BoolT> IsNotEqualInWord32(TNode<Word32T> word32,
3169 typename BitField::FieldType value) {
3170 return Word32BinaryNot(IsEqualInWord32<BitField>(word32, value));
3171 }

3184 // Returns true if any of the mask's bit are set in the given Smi.
3185 // Smi-encoding of the mask is performed implicitly!
3186 TNode<BoolT> IsSetSmi(TNode<Smi> smi, int untagged_mask) {
3187 intptr_t mask_word = base::bit_cast<intptr_t>(Smi::FromInt(untagged_mask));
3188 return WordNotEqual(WordAnd(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(smi),
3189 IntPtrConstant(mask_word)),
3190 IntPtrConstant(0));
3191 }

3447 // Operating mode for TryGetOwnProperty and CallGetterIfAccessor
3448 enum GetOwnPropertyMode {
3449 // kCallJSGetterDontUseCachedName is used when we want to get the result of
3450 // the getter call, and don't use cached_name_property when the getter is
3451 // the function template and it has cached_property_name, which would just
3452 // bailout for the IC system to create a named property handler
3453 kCallJSGetterDontUseCachedName,
3454 // kCallJSGetterUseCachedName is used when we want to get the result of
3455 // the getter call, and use cached_name_property when the getter is
3456 // the function template and it has cached_property_name, which would call
3457 // GetProperty rather than bailout for Generic/NoFeedback load
3458 kCallJSGetterUseCachedName,
3459 // kReturnAccessorPair is used when we're only getting the property
3460 // descriptor
3461 kReturnAccessorPair
3462 };
3463 // Receiver handling mode for TryGetOwnProperty and CallGetterIfAccessor.
3464 enum ExpectedReceiverMode {
3465 // The receiver is guaranteed to be JSReceiver, no conversion is necessary
3466 // in case a function callback template has to be called.
3467 kExpectingJSReceiver,
3468 // The receiver can be anything, it has to be converted to JSReceiver
3469 // in case a function callback template has to be called.
3470 kExpectingAnyReceiver,
3471 };
3472 // Tries to get {object}'s own {unique_name} property value. If the property
3473 // is an accessor then it also calls a getter. If the property is a double
3474 // field it re-wraps value in an immutable heap number. {unique_name} must be
3475 // a unique name (Symbol or InternalizedString) that is not an array index.
3476 void TryGetOwnProperty(
3477 TNode<Context> context, TNode<Object> receiver, TNode<JSReceiver> object,
3478 TNode<Map> map, TNode<Int32T> instance_type, TNode<Name> unique_name,
3479 Label* if_found_value, TVariable<Object>* var_value, Label* if_not_found,
3480 Label* if_bailout,
3481 ExpectedReceiverMode expected_receiver_mode = kExpectingAnyReceiver);
3482 void TryGetOwnProperty(
3483 TNode<Context> context, TNode<Object> receiver, TNode<JSReceiver> object,
3484 TNode<Map> map, TNode<Int32T> instance_type, TNode<Name> unique_name,
3485 Label* if_found_value, TVariable<Object>* var_value,
3486 TVariable<Uint32T>* var_details, TVariable<Object>* var_raw_value,
3487 Label* if_not_found, Label* if_bailout, GetOwnPropertyMode mode,
3488 ExpectedReceiverMode expected_receiver_mode = kExpectingAnyReceiver);

3564 // Generic property lookup generator. If the {object} is fast and
3565 // {unique_name} property is found then the control goes to {if_found_fast}
3566 // label and {var_meta_storage} and {var_name_index} will contain
3567 // DescriptorArray and an index of the descriptor's name respectively.
3568 // If the {object} is slow or global then the control goes to {if_found_dict}
3569 // or {if_found_global} and the {var_meta_storage} and {var_name_index} will
3570 // contain a dictionary and an index of the key field of the found entry.
3571 // If property is not found or given lookup is not supported then
3572 // the control goes to {if_not_found} or {if_bailout} respectively.
3573 //
3574 // Note: this code does not check if the global dictionary points to deleted
3575 // entry! This has to be done by the caller.
3576 void TryLookupProperty(TNode<HeapObject> object, TNode<Map> map,
3577 TNode<Int32T> instance_type, TNode<Name> unique_name,
3578 Label* if_found_fast, Label* if_found_dict,
3579 Label* if_found_global,
3580 TVariable<HeapObject>* var_meta_storage,
3581 TVariable<IntPtrT>* var_name_index,
3582 Label* if_not_found, Label* if_bailout);
3583
3584 // This is a building block for TryLookupProperty() above. Supports only
3585 // non-special fast and dictionary objects.
3586 // TODO(v8:11167, v8:11177) |bailout| only needed for SetDataProperties
3587 // workaround.
3588 void TryLookupPropertyInSimpleObject(TNode<JSObject> object, TNode<Map> map,
3589 TNode<Name> unique_name,
3590 Label* if_found_fast,
3591 Label* if_found_dict,
3592 TVariable<HeapObject>* var_meta_storage,
3593 TVariable<IntPtrT>* var_name_index,
3594 Label* if_not_found, Label* bailout);
3595
3596 // This method jumps to if_found if the element is known to exist. To
3597 // if_absent if it's known to not exist. To if_not_found if the prototype
3598 // chain needs to be checked. And if_bailout if the lookup is unsupported.
3599 void TryLookupElement(TNode<HeapObject> object, TNode<Map> map,
3600 TNode<Int32T> instance_type,
3601 TNode<IntPtrT> intptr_index, Label* if_found,
3602 Label* if_absent, Label* if_not_found,
3603 Label* if_bailout);
3604
3605 // For integer indexed exotic cases, check if the given string cannot be a
3606 // special index. If we are not sure that the given string is not a special
3607 // index with a simple check, return False. Note that "False" return value
3608 // does not mean that the name_string is a special index in the current
3609 // implementation.
3610 void BranchIfMaybeSpecialIndex(TNode<String> name_string,
3611 Label* if_maybe_special_index,
3612 Label* if_not_special_index);
3613
3614 // This is a type of a lookup property in holder generator function. The {key}
3615 // is guaranteed to be an unique name.
3616 using LookupPropertyInHolder = std::function<void(
3617 TNode<HeapObject> receiver, TNode<HeapObject> holder, TNode<Map> map,
3618 TNode<Int32T> instance_type, TNode<Name> key, Label* next_holder,
3619 Label* if_bailout)>;
3620
3621 // This is a type of a lookup element in holder generator function. The {key}
3622 // is an Int32 index.
3623 using LookupElementInHolder = std::function<void(
3624 TNode<HeapObject> receiver, TNode<HeapObject> holder, TNode<Map> map,
3625 TNode<Int32T> instance_type, TNode<IntPtrT> key, Label* next_holder,
3626 Label* if_bailout)>;
3627
3628 // Generic property prototype chain lookup generator.
3629 // For properties it generates lookup using given {lookup_property_in_holder}
3630 // and for elements it uses {lookup_element_in_holder}.
3631 // Upon reaching the end of prototype chain the control goes to {if_end}.
3632 // If it can't handle the case {receiver}/{key} case then the control goes
3633 // to {if_bailout}.
3634 // If {if_proxy} is nullptr, proxies go to if_bailout.
3635 void TryPrototypeChainLookup(
3636 TNode<Object> receiver, TNode<Object> object, TNode<Object> key,
3637 const LookupPropertyInHolder& lookup_property_in_holder,
3638 const LookupElementInHolder& lookup_element_in_holder, Label* if_end,
3639 Label* if_bailout, Label* if_proxy, bool handle_private_names = false);
3640

3644 // due to [[GetPrototypeOf]] invocations.

3961 void GotoIfStringEqual(TNode<String> lhs, TNode<IntPtrT> lhs_length,
3962 TNode<String> rhs, Label* if_true) {
3963 Label if_false(this);
3964 // Callers must handle the case where {lhs} and {rhs} refer to the same
3965 // String object.
3966 CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedNotEqual(lhs, rhs));
3967 TNode<IntPtrT> rhs_length = LoadStringLengthAsWord(rhs);
3968 BranchIfStringEqual(lhs, lhs_length, rhs, rhs_length, if_true, &if_false,
3969 nullptr);
3970
3971 BIND(&if_false);
3972 }
3973
3974 void BranchIfStringEqual(TNode<String> lhs, TNode<String> rhs, Label* if_true,
3975 Label* if_false,
3976 TVariable<Boolean>* result = nullptr) {
3977 return BranchIfStringEqual(lhs, LoadStringLengthAsWord(lhs), rhs,
3978 LoadStringLengthAsWord(rhs), if_true, if_false,
3979 result);
3980 }

3984 Label* if_true, Label* if_false,
3985 TVariable<Boolean>* result = nullptr);

4134
4135 // Indicate that this code must support a dynamic parameter count.
4136 //
4137 // This is used for builtins that must work on functions with different
4138 // parameter counts. In that case, the true JS parameter count is only known
4139 // at runtime and must be obtained in order to compute the total number of
4140 // arguments (which may include padding arguments). The parameter count is
4141 // subsequently available through the corresponding CodeAssembler accessors.
4142 // The target function object and the dispatch handle need to be passed in
4143 // and are used to obtain the actual parameter count of the called function.
4144 //
4145 // This should generally be invoked directly at the start of the function.
4146 //
4147 // TODO(saelo): it would be a bit nicer if this would happen automatically in
4148 // the function prologue for functions marked as requiring this (e.g. via the
4149 // call descriptor). It's not clear if that's worth the effort though for the
4150 // handful of builtins that need this.
4151 void SetSupportsDynamicParameterCount(
4152 TNode<JSFunction> callee, TNode<JSDispatchHandleT> dispatch_handle);
4153
4154 // Figure out the SFI's code object using its data field.
4155 // If |data_type_out| is provided, the instance type of the function data will
4156 // be stored in it. In case the code object is a builtin (data is a Smi),
4157 // data_type_out will be set to 0.
4158 // If |if_compile_lazy| is provided then the execution will go to the given
4159 // label in case of an CompileLazy code object.
4160 TNode<Code> GetSharedFunctionInfoCode(
4161 TNode<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info,
4162 TVariable<Uint16T>* data_type_out = nullptr,
4163 Label* if_compile_lazy = nullptr);

4313 bool ConstexprInt31Equal(int31_t a, int31_t b) { return a == b; }
4314 bool ConstexprInt31NotEqual(int31_t a, int31_t b) { return a != b; }
4315 bool ConstexprInt31GreaterThanEqual(int31_t a, int31_t b) { return a >= b; }
4316 bool ConstexprUint32Equal(uint32_t a, uint32_t b) { return a == b; }
4317 bool ConstexprUint32NotEqual(uint32_t a, uint32_t b) { return a != b; }
4318 bool ConstexprInt32Equal(int32_t a, int32_t b) { return a == b; }
4319 bool ConstexprInt32NotEqual(int32_t a, int32_t b) { return a != b; }
4320 bool ConstexprInt32GreaterThanEqual(int32_t a, int32_t b) { return a >= b; }
4321 uint32_t ConstexprUint32Add(uint32_t a, uint32_t b) { return a + b; }
4322 int32_t ConstexprUint32Sub(uint32_t a, uint32_t b) { return a - b; }
4323 int32_t ConstexprInt32Sub(int32_t a, int32_t b) { return a - b; }
4324 int32_t ConstexprInt32Add(int32_t a, int32_t b) { return a + b; }
4325 int31_t ConstexprInt31Add(int31_t a, int31_t b) {
4326 int32_t val;
4327 CHECK(!base::bits::SignedAddOverflow32(a, b, &val));
4328 return val;
4329 }
4330 int31_t ConstexprInt31Mul(int31_t a, int31_t b) {
4331 int32_t val;
4332 CHECK(!base::bits::SignedMulOverflow32(a, b, &val));
4333 return val;
4334 }

4341 // CSA does not support 64-bit types on 32-bit platforms so as a workaround
4342 // the kMaxSafeIntegerUint64 is defined as uintptr and allowed to be used only
4343 // inside if constexpr (Is64()) i.e. on 64-bit architectures.
4344 static uintptr_t MaxSafeIntegerUintPtr() {
4345#if defined(V8_HOST_ARCH_64_BIT)
4346 // This ifdef is required to avoid build issues on 32-bit MSVC which
4347 // complains about static_cast<uintptr_t>(kMaxSafeIntegerUint64).
4348 return kMaxSafeIntegerUint64;
4349#else
4350 UNREACHABLE();
4351#endif
4352 }

4566 TNode<BoolT> IsPageFlagSet(TNode<IntPtrT> object, int mask) {
4567 TNode<IntPtrT> header = MemoryChunkFromAddress(object);
4568 TNode<IntPtrT> flags = UncheckedCast<IntPtrT>(
4569 Load(MachineType::Pointer(), header,
4570 IntPtrConstant(MemoryChunk::FlagsOffset())));
4571 return WordNotEqual(WordAnd(flags, IntPtrConstant(mask)),
4572 IntPtrConstant(0));
4573 }
4574
4575 TNode<BoolT> IsPageFlagReset(TNode<IntPtrT> object, int mask) {
4576 TNode<IntPtrT> header = MemoryChunkFromAddress(object);
4577 TNode<IntPtrT> flags = UncheckedCast<IntPtrT>(
4578 Load(MachineType::Pointer(), header,
4579 IntPtrConstant(MemoryChunk::FlagsOffset())));
4580 return WordEqual(WordAnd(flags, IntPtrConstant(mask)), IntPtrConstant(0));
4581 }

4739class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE CodeStubArguments {

4750 // struct of values.

4814class ToDirectStringAssembler : public CodeStubAssembler {
4815 private:
4816 enum StringPointerKind { PTR_TO_DATA, PTR_TO_STRING };
4817
4818 public:
4819 enum Flag {
4820 kDontUnpackSlicedStrings = 1 << 0,
4821 };
4822 using Flags = base::Flags<Flag>;
4823
4824 ToDirectStringAssembler(compiler::CodeAssemblerState* state,
4825 TNode<String> string, Flags flags = Flags());
4826
4827 // Converts flat cons, thin, and sliced strings and returns the direct
4828 // string. The result can be either a sequential or external string.
4829 // Jumps to if_bailout if the string if the string is indirect and cannot
4830 // be unpacked.
4831 TNode<String> TryToDirect(Label* if_bailout);
4832
4833 // As above, but flattens in runtime if the string cannot be unpacked
4834 // otherwise.
4835 TNode<String> ToDirect();
4836
4837 // Returns a pointer to the beginning of the string data.
4838 // Jumps to if_bailout if the external string cannot be unpacked.
4839 TNode<RawPtrT> PointerToData(Label* if_bailout) {
4840 return TryToSequential(PTR_TO_DATA, if_bailout);
4841 }
4842
4843 // Returns a pointer that, offset-wise, looks like a String.
4844 // Jumps to if_bailout if the external string cannot be unpacked.
4845 TNode<RawPtrT> PointerToString(Label* if_bailout) {
4846 return TryToSequential(PTR_TO_STRING, if_bailout);
4847 }
4848
4849 TNode<BoolT> IsOneByte();
4850
4851 TNode<String> string() { return var_string_.value(); }
4852 TNode<IntPtrT> offset() { return var_offset_.value(); }
4853 TNode<Word32T> is_external() { return var_is_external_.value(); }
4854
4855 private:
4856 TNode<RawPtrT> TryToSequential(StringPointerKind ptr_kind, Label* if_bailout);
4857
4858 TVariable<String> var_string_;
4859#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
4860 TVariable<Map> var_map_;
4861#else
4862 TVariable<Int32T> var_instance_type_;
4863#endif
4864 // TODO(v8:9880): Use UintPtrT here.
4865 TVariable<IntPtrT> var_offset_;
4866 TVariable<Word32T> var_is_external_;
4867
4868 const Flags flags_;
4869};
